# Penny Lane Documentation Sync

**RULE**: Always update Penny Lane after every GitHub commit/push.

## When to Update

After every `git push` to GitHub, use the `memory_store` tool from the `user-penny-lane` MCP server to document:

- New features or functionality
- Configuration changes
- API changes or new endpoints
- Database schema changes
- Important bug fixes
- Deployment/infrastructure changes

## How to Update

```
CallMcpTool:
  server: user-penny-lane
  toolName: memory_store
  arguments:
    content: "# Feature/Change Title\n\nDescription of what changed..."
    tags: ["relevant", "tags"]
    project: "oracle-loe-reconciler"
```

## Required Fields

- `content`: Markdown description of the change
- `tags`: Array of relevant tags for categorization
- `project`: Always use `"oracle-loe-reconciler"`

## Example

After adding a new API endpoint:

```json
{
  "content": "# New Endpoint: /api/reports/summary\n\nReturns aggregated report data...",
  "tags": ["api", "reports", "endpoint"],
  "project": "oracle-loe-reconciler"
}
```
